Good to hear. To be clear, ARCs/WARCs are written fine no matter what 
versions of Heritrix and the JDK you&#39;re using. The issue that began in 
JDK6u23 affects *reading* them back in record increments. (It also 
causes some of the writing unit tests to fail, but the actual failure is 
on the reading step of the write-then-read-to-check test cycle.)

- Gordon @ IA

